<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<taxonomicName authority="Johnston, 1838" authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1838" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata (Johnston, 1838)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Species complex. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mustaquim, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="75 - 88" title="Morphological variation in Polydoraciliata complex (Polychaeta: Annelida)" volume="86" year="1986">Mustaquim (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mustaquim, Javed" journalOrPublisher="Comparative Biochemistry and Physiology Part B: Comparative Biochemistry" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="197 - 205" title="Electrophoretic variation of isozymes in Polydoraciliata complex (Polychaeta: Spionidae)" volume="91" year="1988">Mustaquim (1988)</bibRefCitation>
provided behavioural (boring and tube-dwelling) and genetic evidence of two forms present under 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
; morphological differences between the forms are also reported. 
<bibRefCitation author="Radashevsky, Vasily I." journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 245" title="The morphology of two sibling sympatric Polydora species (Polychaeta: Spionidae) from the Sea of Japan" volume="86" year="2006">Radashevsky and Pankova (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, regarding European material, assign the tube-dwelling form to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
and the boring form to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora calcarea" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="calcarea">Polydora calcarea</taxonomicName>
(Templeton, 1836). The presence of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
in the Mediterranean was questioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cinar, Melih Ertan" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="821 - 827" title="Alien species of spionid polychaetes (Streblospiogynobranchiata and Polydoracornuta) in Izmir Bay, eastern Mediterranean" volume="85" year="2005">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Çinar">Cinar</normalizedToken>
et al. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Dagli, Ertan" journalOrPublisher="Italian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="49 - 64" title="Spionidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from the Aegean Sea (eastern Mediterranean)" volume="78" year="2011">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dağlı">Dagli</normalizedToken>
et al. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
; but see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Mikac, Barbara" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 17" title="A sea of worms: polychaete checklist of the Adriatic Sea" volume="3943" year="2015">Mikac (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. The former authors suggest that 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
could have been confused with 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora cornuta" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cornuta">Polydora cornuta</taxonomicName>
Bosc, 1802 or 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora agassizii" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="agassizii">Polydora agassizii</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
, 1869; a Mediterranean species synonymised with 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
by Carazzi (1893), but resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Radashevsky, V." journalOrPublisher="Zoological Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="203 - 21" title="Polydora (Polychaeta: Spionidae) species from Taiwan" volume="39" year="2000">Radashevsky and Hsieh (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. Until re-examination of the Greek material is possible, these records are retained under 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Polydora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Polydora ciliata" order="Spionida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="ciliata">Polydora ciliata</taxonomicName>
in this checklist.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
